Comments.Message:
I also got this issue and solved it without the need to recompile the WPFToolkit-Library.

I created a class which inherits from the AutoCompleteBox and write some code to circumvent the described issue :

```
public class MyAutoCompleteBox : AutoCompleteBox
{
	private int selectionStart, selectionLength;
	public TextBox TextBoxPart { get; set; }

	public MyAutoCompleteBox()
	{
		this.PreviewMouseRightButtonUp += (os, ea) =>
									{
										this.selectionStart = TextBoxPart.SelectionStart;
										this.selectionLength = TextBoxPart.SelectionLength;
									};
	}

	protected override void OnIsKeyboardFocusWithinChanged(DependencyPropertyChangedEventArgs e)
	{
		base.OnIsKeyboardFocusWithinChanged( e );

		this.TextBoxPart.SelectionStart = this.selectionStart;
		this.TextBoxPart.SelectionLength = this.selectionLength;
	}

	public override void OnApplyTemplate()
	{
		base.OnApplyTemplate();

		var textBox = this.GetTemplateChild( "Text" ) as TextBox;

		if (textBox != null) this.TextBoxPart = textBox;
	}
}
```

The additional benefit of this new class is, that you have access to the TextBox whenever you need it (in the WPFToolkit the TextBox of the AutoCompleteBox is only internal NOT public).

You can use the new class like the AutoCompleteBox with all the features working.
